["Craig Sibbald (born 18 May 1995) is a Scottish professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Scottish Premiership club Livingston. He has previously played for Falkirk and represented Scotland at under-16 and under-17 level.","Sibbald made his first team debut for Falkirk aged 16, in a 2\u20131 win against Brechin City in the 2011\u201312 Scottish Challenge Cup.[2] This was quickly followed by his first start in the league on 6 August against Raith Rovers.[3]","Sibbald signed a contract extension with Falkirk on 3 July 2014, which contracted him to the club until 2017.[4] He signed a new one-year contract with Falkirk on 11 August 2017, after an unsuccessful trial with Luton Town.[5]","Sibbald signed for newly promoted Scottish Premiership club Livingston on 30 May 2018 on a two-year contract.[6]","Sibbald was capped three times for the Scottish under-16 team from 2010 to 2011.[7] On 17 August 2011, Sibbald was called up to the Scottish under-17 team to participate in the 2011 International Youth Toto Cup.[8] He was capped twice for Scotland at under-17 level in 2012.[7]"]